  "finding": "The body-drain chunk-shape hypothesis is refuted. Every scenario and request count shows both ylong_http_client and libcurl delivering exactly one measured body callback/data chunk per request and exactly 4096 body bytes per request. The remaining HTTPS-origin-over-HTTPS-proxy gap is not explained by benchmark-side body chunk fragmentation.",
